The paper deals with communication networks and queue management algorithms, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of linear network coding also suggests a possible fit in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the concept of feedback, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the comparison of the proposed algorithm with a baseline queuing approach suggests a possible fit in the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
